<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-07-02T05:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-07-02T05:00:00-05:00" n="409" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d409">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">890G.24/36: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Iraq</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Farrell</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Baghdad</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-07-02T13:00:00+03:00">July 2,
                                    1942—1 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 3:37 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>135. My 126 [<hi rend="italic">127</hi>], June 22, 1 p.m. Military
                            mission customs exemption question has been referred by Iraqi Ministry
                            of Finance to Ministry of Justice. Latter on advice of its British legal
                            adviser now informs me that Iraqi Government desires to negotiate a
                            convention with the United States Government to serve as legal basis for
                            legislation to authorize customs franchise. Draft is now in preparation.
                            Meanwhile I request Department’s views and instructions.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Farrell</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>